  "texts": [
    "For instance, bentonite improves workability in higher w/c ratio mixes, which can be advantageous for soil stabilization applications; however, it may reduce workability in low w/c ratio concrete.",
    "Similarly, zeolite and WGP contribute to reduced permeability and increased durability, although these benefits are sensitive to the replacement ratio and particle size.",
    "Finally, some materials, like ESP, can act as fillers, enhancing the concrete microstructure when used at suitable replacement levels.",
    "Fresh properties Silica fume (SF)The study by Sadrmomtazi et al. [42] found that using SF as a replacement material at ratios of 5% to 15% can enhance the workability and flowability of concrete, with improvements of up to 15% at lower SF levels.",
    "However, at higher dosages (such as 15%), workability may decrease."
